main event: A civilian observer witnessed a bright round object emitting a pulsing blue-white light in the sky over Winchester, Virginia on 30 April 1955.
interesting points: The object hovered for approximately 5 minutes before moving erratically in the sky., The observer described the object as several hundred feet in diameter., The sighting lasted around 10 minutes total before the object accelerated and disappeared., The observer reported the sighting to the Winchester police department., This case was classified as confidential under Project Blue Book.
sighted object: a bright round object emitting a pulsing blue-white light
